0.name: testFailed
0.description: indicates the result of the most recently performed test.

bitDecoding.1: the last test failed.

1.name: testFailedThisOperationCycle
1.description: indicates whether or not a diagnostic test has reported a testFailed result at any time during the current operational cycle.

bitDecoding.0: result has not been reported during the current operational cycle.
bitDecoding.1: result was reported at least once during the current operational cycle.

2.name: pendingDTC
2.description: indicates whether or not a diagnostic test has reported a testFailed result at any time during the current or last completed operation cycle.

bitDecoding.0: after an operation cycle test was completed, a malfunction was not detected.
bitDecoding.1: a malfunction was detected during the current operation cycle.

3.name: confirmedDTC
3.description: indicates whether a malfunction was detected enough times to warrant that the DTC is desired to be stored in long-term memory.

bitDecoding.0: DTC has never been confirmed since the last call.
bitDecoding.1: DTC confirmed at least once since the last call.

4.name: testNotCompletedSinceLastClear
4.description: indicates whether a DTC test has ever run and completed since the last time a call was made.

bitDecoding.0: DTC test has returned either a passed or failed test result at least one time since the last time diagnostic info was cleared.
bitDecoding.1: DTC test has not run to completion since the last time diagnostic info was cleared.

5.name: testFailedSinceLastClear
5.description: indicates whether a DTC test has completed with a failed result since the last time a call was made.

bitDecoding.0: DTC test has not indicated a failed result since the last time diagnostic info was cleared.
bitDecoding.1: DTC test returned a failed result at least once since the last time diagnostic info was cleared.

6.name: testNotCompletedThisOperationCycle
6.description: indicates whether a DTC test has ever run and completed during the current operation cycle.

bitDecoding.0: DTC test has returned either a passed or failed result during the current drive cycle.
bitDecoding.1: DTC test was not run to completion this operation cycle.

fileSizeCompressed.description: defines the size of the compressed file in bytes.
